            ('Explain collective ministerial responsibility in the UK and its implications.',
             ['All Cabinet ministers are expected to publicly support government decisions once made, regardless of private disagreements.', 'A minister who publicly dissents must resign — this maintains the appearance of government unity.', 'If the Cabinet loses a vote of no confidence in the Commons, the entire government must resign or call a general election.', 'This mechanism makes the PM accountable to Parliament and ensures disciplined executive decision-making.']),
